      "*   **Flexible Scaling:** Need more processing power or capability? Simply add more agents. This decentralized nature makes scaling your application much more agile and cost-effective compared to traditional monolithic architectures.\n",
      "\n",
      "**2. Increased Robustness and Fault Tolerance:**\n",
      "\n",
      "*   **Decentralized Control:** If one agent fails, others can often continue to function, gracefully handling the situation or even taking over the failed agent's responsibilities. This leads to more resilient applications that can withstand partial failures.\n",
      "*   **Self-Healing Capabilities:** Agents can be programmed to detect issues with their peers and initiate recovery processes or reassignments, leading to systems that can adapt and recover from errors with minimal human intervention.\n",
      "\n",
